1. Definitions

1.1 "License" means this Commercial Open Source Software Manifest.

1.2 "Software" means the software distributed under this License.

1.3 "Source Code" means the preferred form for making modifications to the Software.

1.4 "You" (or "Your") means an individual or legal entity exercising permissions granted by this License.

1.5 "Contributor" means any individual or legal entity that creates, contributes to, or modifies the Software.

1.6 "Commercial Use" means any use of the Software that is intended for or results in commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

1.7 "OSPM" refers to the Opensource Software Package Marketplace (ospm.app).

2. Grant of Rights

2.1. Source Code Availability
The Software must be distributed with the complete corresponding machine-readable Source Code, which must be provided under this License.

2.2. Distribution through OSPM
The Software and any derivative works must be distributed through OSPM. Distribution must be under a subscription model, including monthly, annual, or perpetual subscriptions per seat per project/repository.

2.3. Subscription for Data Use
A separate subscription is required for using the Source Code or any derivative IP as training data for artificial intelligence or any data aggregation use cases.

2.4. Distribution of Derivative Works
Any fork or derivative work must be distributed via OSPM. The full subscription cost for the original work must be reimbursed to the authors of the original work. Authors of derivative works may set their subscription price, which will be charged to the end customer on top of the original license subscription cost.

2.5. Subscription Types and Prices
This License must include the subscription type and price, including any distribution fee collected by OSPM.

2.6. Free Subscription for Non-Commercial Use
The COSS Manifest permits a free-of-charge subscription for non-commercial use, including personal, educational, and research purposes.

